law.text:
The provisions of this subtitle that apply to insurers also apply to:
a corporation that operates a nonprofit health service plan under Title 14, Subtitle 2 of this article;
a dental plan organization as defined in § 14-401 of this article;
a health maintenance organization as defined in Title 19, Subtitle 7 of the Health - General Article;
a surplus lines insurer;
the Maryland Automobile Insurance Fund;
the State when a claim has been filed against the State under Title 12 of the State Government Article;
the State when a claim has been filed against the State under Title 2, Subtitle 5 of the State Personnel and Pensions Article;
the State, including the Uninsured Employers' Fund, when a claim has been filed against the State under Title 9 of the Labor and Employment Article;
the Maryland Transit Administration when acting as a self-insurer under § 7-703 of the Transportation Article;
a third party administrator under Title 8, Subtitle 3 of this article;
a self-insurer under § 17-103(a)(2) of the Transportation Article;
the Maryland Health Insurance Plan; and
an agent, employee, or representative of an entity described in items (1) through (12) of this section.
